      • shape

        public long[] shape()
        Convenience method, similar to sizes().vec().get(). Returns a new long[] with each call since e.g. transpose_() and squeeze_() can change the shape of the tensor, and the caller could otherwise modify the contents, surprising subsequent callers. Please memoize externally if you're concerned about performance.
